  fhir:description [ fhir:v "Morphology group codes used in the Multiple Primary Tester data quality check. Groups are derived from morphology codes using the mapping logic defined in the CanReg5 DefaultMultiplePrimaryTester class. Groups 8-14 represent haematopoietic/lymphoid tissue subtypes (systemic groups). Group 0 indicates an invalid morphology, and group 17 indicates an unspecified morphology."] ; # 
